# Design Workflow

- For UI, onboarding, pricing, dashboard, checkout, settings, or paywall work, gather real product references before inventing patterns.
- Use Lazyweb for pricing page references, onboarding research, UI comparisons, and improvements to existing designs.
- When a Figma file or URL is provided, inspect the design first and adapt it to the project's existing components, tokens, and layout conventions.
- Prefer existing project components and design tokens over new one-off styles.
- Treat screenshots and Figma output as reference material; produce production-ready code that fits the target project.
- For larger design tasks, consider parallel subagents for reference research, Figma analysis, component mapping, and review.
- Call out missing states, accessibility risks, responsive behavior, and test gaps before considering a design task complete.
